discussion.content:
The first question should be No because It would only have been possible by registering an image, which I have not seen indicated in the statement or in the code. 

The statement indicates the following: 
Plug-ins registered on the update of the Person of interest field (this field is in the contact entity) must send an email notification when the candidate named in the email is a person of interest.

With this in mind, the plug-in is triggered when the "Person of Interest" field has been updated. According to the plug-in code the only way to get the fullname field is to have registered an image of type PostImage and do the following:
Entity postContact = (Entity)context.PostEntityImages["Image"];
string contactName= postContact .GetAttributeValue<string>("fullname");
